higher ticket prices strong longrunning 
musicals several acclaimed new plays helped broadway end its 
season with a record boxoffice take 
theaters took in 262 million up 4 percent over the 198889 
seasons total of 253 million according to figures released 
tuesday 
the league of american theaters and producers also said 
attendance was 8 million off slightly from last seasons record 
81 million but still higher than the 7 million of two years ago 
it was a good season it had strong boxoffice dollars and 
solid attendance said george wachtel the leagues director of 
research there were fewer musicals but there were more plays 
over the last four years it was one of the best seasons 
attendancewise 
much of the boxoffice strength came from longrunning musicals 
particularly the phantom of the opera and les miserables 
each grossing more than 500000 a week and other veteran hits 
like cats and me and my girl 
the only new musical to demonstrate much boxoffice muscle is 
jerome robbins broadway which has been running at slightly 
under capacity since it opened in january the compilation of dance 
numbers from some of the choreographers biggest hits has been 
grossing about 520000 a week 
it also has a top ticket price of 55 
the average ticket price rose from 3110 to 3390 up 6 
percent from last year the league said much of the rise wachtel 
said was because theatergoers were paying full price for tickets 
to hot shows like phantom and les miserables which are not 
available at halfprice discount 
only seven musicals including a revival of aint misbehavin 
opened on broadway during the 198889 season compared with 15 
the previous year they included such flops as legs diamond 
chu chem and welcome to the club as well as such 
stillrunning shows as black and blue and starmites 
for a variety of reasons its becoming increasingly difficult 
to mount a large musical wachtel said but i do look to the 
fact that there were two seasons fairly recently when there was as 
many as 20 musicals you have to be optimistic to be in this 
business and we are 
twentyone plays including nine revivals opened on broadway 
during the 198889 season among the biggest successes were neil 
simons farce rumors and wendy wassersteins the heidi 
chronicles which is the favorite to win the best play tony on 
june 4 
