leonora in il trovatore 
she sang more than 400 performances with the met until retiring 
at age 59 she was one of the few principal singers to inaugurate 
two successive seasons for the company in 1951 and 1952 
she enjoyed a successful concert career and recorded widely in 
the italian repertoire especially works by verdi and puccini 
