students and swelled to more than 200000 before tapering off 
the students many from outlying provinces and most of them 
broke rely on donations for their meals usually a couple of buns 
twice a day sometimes with rice porridge and a bottle of chalky 
soda pop 
look how cracked my lips are said a rower from beijing 
physical education university i collapsed once during the hunger 
strike whats hardest is keeping up our strength 
its easier to stay up all night because of the cold the rower 
said if i sleep at night i get the chills he said squatting 
on a thick cotton jacket on tiananmens concrete pavement 
overnight temperatures drop to 52 degrees 
the food situation has improved lately said chen shounan of 
anhui industry institute the last couple of days we each got an 
egg with our meals 
the lamps glowing in the square go out around 515 am and the 
nights wind down with the raising of the national flag by a 
peoples liberation army honor guard at sunrise 
you see we are a patriotic movement nothing more said a 
beijing agricultural institute coed who stayed up to join about 100 
others and applaud the flagraising i may lose sleep but its 
worth it 
