since desai has acknowledged being a public figure the judge 
added in a written opinion that to apply indian defamation law or 
any other foreign defamation law at odds with the first amendment 
could have a tremendous chilling effect 
legal experts say norgles ruling is the first of its kind and 
signals protections for us authors speechmakers and publishers 
whose domestically produced works are later published or 
distributed abroad 
