<TEXT>
here are excerpts from boris n yeltsins speech 
wednesday to the congress of peoples deputies as translated by 
the associated press 
on devolution of power 
at the congress the most important question is being decided on 
which the future of our society depends the question of power 
which by rights must belong to the people in the form of the organ 
it elects that is the congress of peoples deputies the central 
committee plenum just before the congress opened did not support my 
suggestion to transfer power somehow at this very first congress 
from the party to the soviets local parliaments the plenum 
decided to recommend for leading posts the same people who have not 
managed to get the society out of crises in politics the economy 
finances the standard of living 
on limited powers of the congress 
the congress which had to take into its hands the power for 
perestroika and the transformation of society has ended up as 
hostage to laws and decisions taken by the previous supreme soviet 
formed back in the times of stagnation 
important questions of state power and administration which 
logically should have been reviewed by the congress were 
decided in advance and it is proposed that we vote in favor of 
these laws 
in these conditions there is a danger of the supreme soviet and 
its presidium turning into an apparatus or lets say half an 
apparatus under the president 
the state of the nation 
the situation in the country is extremely alarming 
antiperestroika forces have become active and are consolidating 
the shadow economy is growing corruption and crime are on the 
rise the moral standards of society are becoming diluted the 
problems of youth are getting sharper the principles of social 
justice and social equality are not being realized the number of 
poor people is growing the soviet peoples belief in the real 
results of perestroika is falling the contradictions in ethnic 
problems are getting sharper the decisions on the food problem 
are being delayed 
the disorganization of the internal market inflation queues 
ration coupons the threat of a financial collapse has become real 
the commandadministrative system has not been broken power still 
belongs to the party apparatus and the bureaucracy 
the vast system of power is profitable only for this apparatus 
the promised program and the promises of the last four years 
have not been fulfilled people live worse such political 
evaluations of the current moment and some of the selfcriticism in 
the speech of comrade gorbachev do not remove him in my opinion 
from responsibility for all of that 
on troops attacking protesters in tbilisi 
a year after the party conference supporting the course for 
democratization we have hit out at meetings and demonstrations 
with one decree at glasnost with a second with a third we 
approved the use of special forces against our own people 
exactly in this atmosphere of creating extraordinary bans by 
law and especially recently such crimes as in tbilisi became 
possible i was there and i am convinced that it was a crime a 
crime against our own people 
in order to calm people down a bit it is necessary to say at 
the congress who in the center took the decision since the 
leadership knows this 
on glasnost 
to guarantee broader democratization and glasnost lets not 
hamper their development as is already happening in fact a law 
on the press should be adopted and the mass media should not 
be organs of the party they should become more and more 
independent 
on priorities 
first of all it is necessary to consider at the congress of 
peoples deputies the tasks and goals of the society and taking 
them into account to form a commission to work on a draft of a new 
constitution i consider it one of the tasks to decisively 
decentralize power and economy to dismantle the 
commandadministrative system which is the source of the menace 
that we would return to the past 
on social justice and the privileged nomenklatura 
without delay laws on pensions on poverty on ecology and on 
forms of property should be adopted in the existing circumstances 
the congress should first of all adopt state programs on how to 
take the country out of crisis the program should be a program of 
urgent measures for more than 70 years we have not managed to 
solve the question of social justice theres every reason to speak 
of an elite existing in our society which is building socialism 
why are there tens of millions of people in this country who live 
below all possible levels of poverty while others bask in luxury 
the defense of the less welltodo and the defenseless layers of 
society should be made a principle of socialist justice 
to begin with taking into account the deficit maybe we should 
cancel all unlawful principles for the nomenklatura and in 
general remove from our lexicon this word nomenklatura this 
would raise the moral level of our society it is necessary to fix 
a minimum standard of living and already at this congress we 
should decide at least one concrete social issue otherwise people 
wont understand us for example we should create a free supply of 
medicines free public transport for the disabled and those below 
the poverty line to solve the pension question at least in part 
i hand over to the presidium of the congress a legislative 
initiative drafted and signed by a large group of deputies 
before we solve all issues of medical care it is necessary to 
transform the fourth medical department the special department 
that provides medical care for the elite into a department caring 
for mothers and their children this should be done for the sake of 
our future in order not to have a situation where infant mortality 
is twice that of any civilized country 
about president mikhail s gorbachev 
i cannot help voicing here one of my concerns the congress 
constitution and the party entrusted the head of state with 
extremely broad authority here we can perceive a troubling 
tendency against the background of a deteriorating economy and the 
sharpening of social issues we see an increase of personal 
influence and personal power in the hands of the head of state 
this can lead to the temptation to solve our complex problems with 
force and we can again find ourselves in the sway of a new 
authoritarian regime a new dictatorship without noticing it 
moreover for 70 years we have not accumulated experience 
either through the party parliament or people of controlling the 
activity of the head of state i think within the limits of 
building a state based on law the present congress should create 
certain collective mechanisms as one of the elements of such a 
mechanism i suggest adopting a law on an annual referendum on 
peoples confidence in the chairman of the supreme soviet of the 
ussr the president 
</TEXT>
