<TEXT>
the sixth earl of enniskillen a longtime resident 
of kenya and a former legislator there has died in scotland at the 
age of 70 
he died tuesday after a short illness at a hospital in perth 
near his home in amulree according to family friend hamish 
carlton 
born david lowry cole in kenya and educated at eton and at 
cambridge university he earned a degree in agriculture and was a 
farmer in kenya and in northern ireland before retiring to scotland 
cole was a captain in the irish guards during world war ii and 
served in british colonial kenya during the 195355 emergency 
caused by an uprising of the mau mau a kikuyu tribal secret 
society against the government european settlers and kikuyu who 
remained loyal to the administration 
cole owned a 100000acre ranch near mount kenya and was a 
member of the kenya national farmers union and vice chairman of the 
kenya stockowners council 
he became provincial commandant of the kenya police service and 
was made a member of the order of british empire by queen elizabeth 
ii in 1955 
from 1961 to 1963 cole was a member of the kenya legislative 
council the legislature of the colony and protectorate of kenya 
before it achieved independence in december 1963 
lord cole succeeded his uncle the fifth earl in 1963 and moved 
to northern ireland where the seat of the earldom is in 
enniskillen county fermanagh there he was a captain in the ulster 
defense regiment the british provinces locally raised security 
force 
survivors include his son and heir andrew viscount cole who 
lives in nairobi and his daughter lady linda muir who lives in 
scotland they are the children of his first marriage to the late 
sonia syers his second wife americanborn nancy henderson 
maclennan also survives 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

