<TEXT>
jerry nachman a columnist for the new york 
post was appointed today as the newspapers new editor 
nachman succeeds jane amsterdam who was relieved on tuesday of 
her duties as editor by the tabloids owner and publisher peter 
kalikow 
ms amsterdam former editor of the magazine manhattan inc 
was the papers editor for 50 weeks 
before nachman joined the post he had worked as general manager 
for the nbcowned television station in washington and news 
director at wnbctv in new york 
his appointment was announced in the papers newsroom 
kalikows spokesman howard rubenstein said no specific 
incident precipitated the change its been under consideration 
for a while and kalikow felt he needed someone new to take the 
post to the next level he said 
it had been reported that there was friction between the editor 
and publisher over a decision to cut back the size of the tabloids 
sunday edition which has lost millions since it was introduced in 
march 
in a statement issued by rubenstein kalikow said he was pleased 
with the progress the post had made under ms amsterdam she has 
worked hard and intelligently and she leaves the post with many 
achievements she will always have my respect and high regard he 
said 
in the same statement ms amsterdam was quoted as saying that 
she departs with great sadness the paper came a long way 
achieving new energy and respectability 
rubenstein said ms amsterdam had not decided what she would do 
next 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

