<TEXT>
foreign minister sousuke uno chosen wednesday by 
governing party leaders to be the next prime minister and lead the 
government from unprecedented crisis is seen as an experienced but 
weak politician 
uno was the second choice of the liberal democratic party to 
succeed prime minister noboru takeshita party leaders tried to 
persuade the partys executive council chairman masayoshi ito 75 
to take the job but he refused citing poor health and 
dissatisfaction with the partys handling of reforms 
few leaders within the scandalridden liberal democratic party 
sang the praises of the 66yearold uno and many put forward 
lastminute alternatives to his nomination such as collective 
rather than individual leadership 
many fear he cannot win back public confidence in the 
government shaken by an influencepeddling scandal that forced 
takeshita to step down and led to charges against 17 politicians 
bureaucrats and businessmen 
analysts speculated that party bosses who are too tainted by 
the financial scandal to take the post now settled on uno as an 
interim leader who will allow them to exert influence and not upset 
their future aspirations 
even the conservative yomiuri shimbun japans largest 
newspaper described uno who has been foreign minister since 1987 
as only a reasonable choice 
some party leaders would have preferred that the successor to 
prime minister takeshita come from the junior ranks in order to 
revitalize the party but uno was chosen to maintain party 
harmony yomiuri said in an editorial 
former prime ministers zenko suzuki and takeo fukuda suggested a 
group leadership and expressed fears uno may be too weak to steer 
the conservative party to victory in parliamentary elections this 
summer 
support for the liberal democrats has fallen to the lowest 
levels ever largely because of the scandal in which the recruit 
co a publishing conglomerate allegedly won government favors by 
handing out millions of dollars in political donations and 
underpriced stock 
though uno is untainted by the scandal he is closely allied 
with former prime minister yasuhiro nakasone under whose 198287 
tenure the influencepeddling allegedly occurred 
the proximity of the two has damaged unos reputation and it 
almost cost him the party nomination analysts say on sunday 
nakasone resigned from the party partly to relieve pressure on uno 
but supporters say unos highranking cabinet posts in a country 
striving for a stronger international role have made him a familiar 
figure to the japanese public and that in itself will bring votes 
to the party 
uno has headed the ministry of international trade and industry 
the defense agency and the science and technology agency he is a 
10term member of the lower house of parliament from shiga 
prefecture in western japan 
born aug 27 1922 into a wealthy family in shiga uno fought 
in world war ii and served on the asian mainland before being taken 
prisoner by soviet troops in northern korea he and his wife 
chiyo have two children a son and daughter 
</TEXT>
