israeli troops today shot and killed three 
guerrillas on the border with lebanon the army command said it 
was the third attempted infiltration in four days 
also today police in lebanon said israeli warplanes attacked 
targets on the outskirts of the southern city of sidon in the fifth 
such attack this year there were no details on casualties 
soldiers shot and killed a 20yearold palestinian in a clash in 
the gaza town of khan yunis and wounded eight other palestinians in 
clashes in the occupied west bank and gaza strip arab doctors said 
and israeli news reports said police had detained six jewish 
settlers suspected of killing a 13yearold arab girl during a 
rampage through a west bank village 
the army said two palestinians from gaza died of wounds suffered 
in earlier clashes it was checking the arab reports of todays 
casualties in the occupied territories 
the border incident occurred near the lebanese village of hula 
about a mile west of the israeli town of kiryat shemona said a 
military spokesman 
he said troops spotted the three guerrillas opened fire and 
killed them immediately the spokesman who cannot be identified 
according to army regulations said the israelis suffered no 
casualties 
security sources said the area has been the site of increased 
troop activity in recent days and reporters observed flares there 
on tuesday a guerrilla was shot to death in southern lebanon 
after being spotted by israeli troops and their south lebanese 
militia allies east of the lebanese town of marjayoun 
troops also killed two guerrillas sunday after several rockets 
were fired into the israeli border town of metulla two more 
guerillas were captured and two escaped the army said 
sundays raid was claimed by george habashs popular front for 
the liberation of palestine and the late talaat yacoubs 
damascusbased palestine liberation front 
arab doctors did not identify the palestinian reported shot and 
killed today the other two palestinians who died of wounds 
suffered earlier 14 were identified by arab news reports as ahmed 
ibrahim nawas 18 who was shot tuesday and mohammed ali al 
farajani 15 wounded may 14 both were shot in the head 
the deaths raised to 502 the number of palestinians killed in 
the nearly 18month uprising against israeli occupation of the west 
bank and gaza strip twentytwo israelis have also been killed 
 
the army meanwhile has started using a new bullet against 
palestinian demonstrators in the occupied lands to help reduce 
fatalities caused by plastic bullets the israeli daily maariv 
reported 
the newspaper said the socalled stun bullet is designed not 
to penetrate the body but it quoted unidentified army commanders 
as saying the bullet can kill if fired improperly it said two 
deaths have been attributed to the new bullet 
the newspaper did not provide further details an army spokesman 
declined immediate comment 
according to army figures 77 palestinians have been killed by 
plastic bullets since they were introduced 10 months ago in some 
cases because the bullets were fired contrary to regulations 
also today palestinians throughout the occupied lands observed 
a general strike ordered by moslem fundamentalists to protest what 
they called prime minister yitzhak shamirs curse against the 
prophet mohammed 
the strike referred to a newspaper interview in which shamir 
warned israel must not make territorial concessions to the 
palestinians because someone might try to cheat us to lie to 
us 
someone might say lets cheat the israelis just like 
mohammed did the palestinians always bring these examples of how 
mohammed used all sorts of ruses to overcome his opponents 
shamir told the jerusalem post in an interview published earlier 
this month 
police meanwhile detained six jewish settlers accused of 
killing a palestinian girl and wounding two others in a rampage 
monday in the west bank village of kifil harith 
the suspects were identified as seminarians at josephs tomb 
yeshiva in nablus 12 miles away 
the hadashot daily said the six would be brought before a judge 
and charged within a few days 
