<TEXT>
the nato allies have patched up an 
unsettling quarrel over shortrange missiles and president bush has 
come to west germany and declared us friendship with the germans 
the two events have lifted chancellor helmut kohl out of the 
political doldrums and given west germans a feeling of pride and 
emerging prominence and in two weeks kohl will be welcoming 
president mikhail s gorbachev of the soviet union for a summit 
it is a dramatic change 
only a few days ago west germans were in a quandary about the 
corner theyd painted themselves into challenging nato policy and 
the united states by insisting on negotiations to remove 
shortrange nuclear missiles from europe 
but the nato summit in brussels produced an compromise agreement 
and allowed bush and kohl to conduct their twoday summit like best 
friends 
the relationship between the united states and the federal 
republic of germany has never been better bush said repeatedly 
during his visit 
the leaders referred often to the first years after world war 
ii stoking the emotional embers still burning in many older west 
germans who recall the american role in rebuilding their nation 
after the fall of hitlers third reich 
the nostalgic theme struck the chord it intended compounding 
west germans satisfaction over the brussels success with a 
reassurance that the americans are still on their side 
bushs visit was a time of celebration for west germans who are 
at once pleased to have made their point with nato partners and 
relieved that it didnt cost them any standing with the alliance 
while many west germans are opposed to nuclear weapons in their 
country they are fearful of isolation and vulnerability should 
they stray too far from their traditional allies 
no nukes no troops is the warning one senior us official 
says he has delivered to west german authorities it raised the 
possibility that if the battlefield nuclear weapons are removed the 
thousands of american and british soldiers in west germany would 
soon follow 
the nato compromise seemed to blow away the concern and it was 
all smiles at the highprofile presidential visit 
