the compromise reached in brussels was engineered by the americans 
to rescue kohl from his political woes 
should kohl lose power during the federal elections in december 
1990 the us government would likely be confronted with a 
coalition of liberals more skeptical of american and nato policies 
kohl seemed to acknowledge the brussels outcome as a gift 
thanking bush for making it possible 
an unusually ebullient kohl described bush to the press as a 
proven friend who has always stood ready to help me in difficult 
times 
asked by reporters whether the brussels compromise would improve 
his reelection chances the chancellor who usually bristles at 
such questions beamed and declared confidently i am completely 
certain as to the results of the elections in 1990 
