<TEXT>
an 8monthold boy who was shot in the head by 
israeli soldiers lay unconscious in a hospital wednesday suffering 
from severe brain damage and breathing through a respirator 
the shooting highlighted the dispute between palestinians who 
say troops fire at demonstrators without regard for innocents and 
israeli officials who say women and children are put in the front 
lines to serve as shields and win publicity for the palestinian 
uprising 
the army confirmed that the infant mohammed hamdan kassem was 
shot by troops in the west bank refugee camp of tulkarem on 
tuesday it said the incident was under investigation 
arab reporters said clashes occurred at the camp on tuesday 
night following a march and that several people were wounded 
the jerusalem post newspaper quoted palestinian sources as 
saying mohammed was struck when his mother samira kassem 
participated in the march with the boy in her arms 
mrs kassem said she was carrying the child down an alley when 
he was hit by a stray bullet she said she did not see any clashes 
at the time 
i felt blood on his head the soldiers were about 100 yards 
away at the end of the street i shouted he was hit he was hit 
and then i ran away she said 
mrs kassem 23 was slumped on a bed outside her sons room at 
mukassed hospital in jerusalem inside mohammed lay unconscious 
the left side of his head covered by a bandage and the right side 
of his body paralyzed 
he kicked with his left foot as a nurse cleared his nasal 
passage 
he suffered severe brain damage we removed a large portion of 
contused brain tissue if he survives he will have all kinds of 
disabilities said dr wahib dajani chief anesthesiologist in 
the intensive care unit 
he displayed the tip of a plastic bullet that pierced the 
childs brain and was removed from his skull 
dajani said mohammed was the youngest victim of the palestinian 
uprising to be treated at the hospital he said the average age of 
shooting victims has decreased in recent months and that more and 
more children and teenagers were among the wounded 
the shooting of mohammed renewed the debate over the armys 
firing practices during the nearly 18monthold rebellion against 
the israeli occupation of the west bank and gaza strip 
the uprising has claimed 502 palestinian lives twentytwo 
israelis also have been killed 
the palestinianrun human rights information center said 34 arab 
children under 5 have been killed by troops during the uprising 
including 29 who died from tear gas inhalation and three who were 
shot to death 
palestinians and human rights activists argue that troops fire 
wildly to break up protests often hitting bystanders that include 
young children 
the wounding of mohammed undoubtedly resulted from the armys 
indiscriminate shooting said fayez abu rahme a palestinian 
lawyer and plo supporter from gaza city 
a senior army official blamed plo activists for making cynical 
use of children in demonstrations 
by getting children killed you get more publicity and that 
keeps the uprising alive which is what the inciters want what 
better way is there than to get a child killed every day said 
col ranaan gissin deputy army spokesman 
he said young children were used as shields also to protect 
adult activists especially when plastic bullets are fired at the 
knees of demonstrators 
the responsibility for the children being there is that of the 
parents and the activists he said 
gissin said that in some cases women and children were wounded 
while walking near the scenes of clashes but that the number of 
such cases was minuscule when compared to the pattern of using 
children on purpose 
faisal husseini a leading palestinian intellectual and 
politican in jerusalem rejected the claim that children were used 
as shields 
there is no way someone is sending children to protect 
himself it is just propaganda coming from people who think they 
have more human feelings than we do he said 
under army regulations soldiers are barred from firing plastic 
bullets at children under age 16 
yossi sarid a liberal member of parliament said that while 
palestinians had used children as propaganda instruments the army 
in many instances had disregarded standing orders on opening fire 
this is the tragedy that the children have to pay for the 
blindness and stupidity of their elders he said 
