<TEXT>
despite wrights pledge to hold onto inner peace his temper is 
legion a former golden gloves boxer he once threatened to punch 
out rep dan lungren rcalif on the house floor when rep pete 
stark dcalif cursed at him wright promptly invited him outside 
to settle the issue 
wrights climb through the ranks was rooted more than anything 
else in sheer hard political work in the four years preceding 
his election as speaker he traveled to more than 250 congressional 
districts raising more than 1 million for candidates collecting 
chits 
his own political history runs the democratic gamut first 
parochial and populist then increasingly liberal he was one of a 
few southern congressmen who refused to sign a petition opposing 
the supreme courts 1954 desegregation decision but he voted 
against the 1964 civil rights act he evolved into a national 
democrat preaching fairness and help for the downtrodden but 
retaining a downhome interest in protecting banks and oil 
operators he favored a strong defense but led the fight against 
the mx missile and aid to the nicaraguan rebels 
craig raupe a former aide who died last october once said 
wright was as complicated as lyndon johnson just not as mean 
even gingrich was once something of a fan he makes everyone 
feel part of the institution the georgia republican said in 
1986 i remember asking him once for floor time he could have 
finessed me instead he took 30 minutes and gave me 30 minutes 
things like that if he does it draw 90 percent of the poison out 
of this place 
wright was born on dec 22 1922 in weatherford he father ran 
national trades day inc a profitable small business that 
specialized in arranging promotional gimmicks like sack races and 
pieeating contests for local merchants young jim was educated in 
the public schools for fort worth and dallas 
my goal he once said was to be a football coach but in 
my junior year in high school i injured my knee and the coach 
suggested that since i couldnt play football what they really 
needed was somebody to represent the school in debate and since he 
was also the world history teacher i was forever trying to impress 
him with how smart i was i got hooked 
at age 19 wright dropped out of the university of texas to 
become a b24 bomber pilot in the pacific where he won a 
distinguished flying cross and the legion of merit at age 23 he 
ran unopposed for the state legislature served as mayor of 
weatherford from 1951 to 1954 and at age 32 was a member of 
congress 
now 34 years later this is his darkest hour but he still has 
the light of his life betty to whom he wrote for their 14th 
christmas together 
youre the dearest truest part of every day i live 
the thought of you within my heart is all it takes to give 
me hope that i can work and learn and grow 
yet grateful be for i have more than any man i know 
for it is true in all i do 
it isnt i its we 
in all of this i do thank you 
for not giving up on me 
