populist firebrand boris n yeltsin urged the new 
parliament wednesday to take power and end 72 years of communist 
party rule he blamed the party and president mikhail s gorbachev 
for continuing economic decline 
yeltsin a member of the party leadership told fellow deputies 
of the congress of peoples deputies that the presidency is 
accumulating too much power and could become a dictatorship 
the congress must take power into its own hands if the 
political and economic restructuring begun by gorbachev is to 
succeed yeltsin said on the sixth day of the popularly elected 
parliaments inaugural session 
