the senate approved legislation wednesday 
aimed at encouraging television networks local stations and cable 
systems to reduce graphic depictions of violence drug use and sex 
on tv 
the bill by sen paul simon dill was approved on a voice 
vote after an amendment by sen jesse helms rnc was adopted to 
include depictions of sexual acts in addition to drug use and 
violence in any guidelines the industry might develop 
technically the bill only exempts the industry from antitrust 
claims that might result from joint efforts to develop the 
guidelines but its passage was clearly aimed at sending a signal 
to the industry that some depictions of violence and sex have 
become too graphic 
network executives did not embrace the measure but they also did 
not try to stop it the american civil liberties union however 
opposed it as a step toward censorship and a threat to first 
amendment rights of free speech 
