european commission vice president announced the resumption of 
talks in a joint communique released here and in paris the talke 
are to be held in brussels belgium 
the issues of how standards will be set and what they will be 
is a top concern of the american business community mosbacher 
said in a statement released by the commerce department with 
this agreement to establish a dialogue we have made significant 
progress toward easing that concern 
the 12 nations comprising the european community have agreed to 
remove trade barriers in 1992 and operate as a single 4 trillion 
market with 320 million consumers some government and business 
leaders fear the regulations and technical standards being written 
for the transition could result in barriers against us goods 
mosbacher and bangemann who met tuesday in brussels where 
president bush was attending the nato summit agreed that products 
imported into the new european market would have the same access to 
testing and certification procedures as european products 
