international business machines corp said 
wednesday it has produced the worlds fastest experimental 
millionbit memory chip at a factory in yasu japan 
the dynamic random access memory chip or dram was made on an 
existing production line demonstrating that it could be 
manufactured in large volumes ibm said it did not say when volume 
prouction might begin 
the chip can retrieve a unit or bit of information in 22 
billionths of a second making it two to three times as fast as the 
current generation of millionbit chips ibm said it can store the 
equivalent of about 100 pages of doublespaced typewritten text 
dram chips are still slower than their more expensive cousins 
static random access memory chips or srams but ibm said the new 
chip shows the gap is narrowing 
last week ibm announced its plant in essex junction vt was 
manufacturing the worlds fastest millionbit dram that is in 
volume production that chip will be used in its as400 business 
computer 
