to take over holly farms since last october and the battle has 
been tied up in hartnetts court since holly and conagra announced 
a previous merger proposal last november 
holly shareholders rejected that proposal in april but an 
asset option agreement included in the plan still is at issue 
in the continuing debate 
the asset agreement allows conagra to purchase about a third of 
holly farms if the company is bought by someone else 
tysons challenge of the asset agreement is expected to go to 
trial but no trial date has been set 
observers of the holly farms battle say the memphis company 
likely would function as an independent subsidiary with conagra 
while the same would not be true with tyson 
